content:
@Claudio Pisani -- symmetric multicategories might be useful to prove @John Baez conjectures
regarding Cartesian Monoidal and Symmetric Monoidal categories, since there are restrictions to both of those classes from Mlt\sf MltMlt.

Here is the Dropbox folder containing the recordings of all the talks. Inside you can see a folder "Claudio Pisani May 22, 2024" where you can find the audio, video, etc. of @Claudio Pisani's talk! Thanks again, Claudio, lot of stuff to think over there.

On Mac, VLC or mplayer usually seem to be able to figure out how to align the audio+video from zoom recordings, and it "just works". Nonetheless if anyone runs into difficulties replaying the talk, please reach out and hopefully someone can help you! :)
@Eric M Downes I couldn't see a file for slides? is it there?
Good point! There is only the video+audio. @Claudio Pisani if you are ok to provide them, can you post a link to your slides as a pdf here, or send them to me and I can add them to the folder?
I just send you my slides, so you can add them to the folder, thank you
Slides uploaded to same directory as video/audio/etc
